This paper proposes a novel meta-RL strategy that involves deep network agents and a task encoder. The paper focuses on improving the efficiency of learning novel tasks, which is a common problem in RL. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions the use of self-supervised reward shaping, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
